# Shell scripts must be LF so they run on Linux/WSL regardless of the cloner's
# core.autocrlf setting (a CRLF shebang breaks bash with a \r error).
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
# Notebooks are JSON stored LF in the index; pin the working tree to LF too so a
# Windows checkout (autocrlf) doesn't show every line as a phantom CRLF diff, and
# so run-bundle provenance isn't spuriously marked repo-dirty.
*.ipynb text eol=lf

# A committed run bundle is frozen evidence — treat every file as binary so git
# never rewrites line endings (byte-exact logs) and never phantom-diffs it.
results/bundles/** -text
